ay we had some serious problems.  First off, you cannot defeat a dragon with only one Enchanter.  And since that's all we had, we were screwed from the beginning.  Yours truly was nominated by the raid leader to be the one to aggro the room (only the gods know why they decided to name me).  Being this was my first time on a Vox raid, I was a little confused on what i was to be doing.  So i go up a ramp thinking it lead to Vox's lair, but instead fell through a trap in the floor and was immediately attacked by lots of hungry giant polar bears.  Luckily i managed to Feign Death with about a half bubble of health left.  The raid leader unfortunately made the same mistake by following me.  He did not survive the polar bears so we lost out leader before the raid even began <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   He never even made it back to take part in the raid.  I felt really bad since it was my fault that he died.  So, someone else pulled Vox's lair and they managed to clear it out.  After about 10 minutes of being FD, the bears forgot about me and i was able to gate back up and take part in the attack.  We rushed into Vox's lair and were met with the typical mass fear, which sent a whole lot of people running for their lives uncontrollably.<br>
She was going down relatively slow and was dealing out an enormous amount of damage.  When she got down to about 25% health she cast her CH and went right back up.  At that point the new leader issued the retreat.  And the CR began.  Always a fun time dragging out 25+ bodies from underneath a Dragon.  <br>
<br>
My take on the raid:  <br>
1.  Too few enchanters.  Only one just won't cut it against Vox.<br>
<br>
2.  Too few healers.  We only had 2 clerics on the whole raid.  I think we had 1 more shaman in there and 1 Druid<br>
<br>
3.  Lack of experience.  The reason why i was picked initially to pull the room was because i was the only person on the entire raid that could FD.  One of the clerics admitted to us that the cleric belonged to a guildmate and he had no clue how to play a cleric.  <br>
<br>
According to what i heard from Kaymar, Vox has now won FIVE raids in a row.  She's on a roll.  <br>
<br>
Ghoulik Bloodmoon<br>
Lvl 51 Heretic<br>
I will see that blasted dragon go down...eventually. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/unumtini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Numtini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>RA Council Assistant<br><font color=blue>Moderator<b></span><br>  Posts: 324<br> <font color=#006400>(7/23/01 11:07:47 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Last night's Vox raid</span><hr size=1> You know, I realize those in a failed raid may want to bonk me for this, but it's really nice to see the monsters winning once in a while. Especially given them elaborate tactics that have been worked out to, well, almost automate the big raids, it just seems nice that once in a while the bull wins. <p>Numtini Lightheart <br>
